==English==
===Pronunciation===
*päst, /pɑːst/, /<tt>pA:st</tt>/
*:'''Homophones''': [[pass]]ed
*:[[Rhymes:English:-ɑːst|Rhymes: -ɑːst]]

===Noun===
'''past'''

#The [[period]] of [[time]] that has [[already]] happened, in contrast to the [[present]] and the [[future]].
#(''grammar'') The [[past tense]].

====Translations====
*French: (1, 2): [[passé#French|passé]] ''m''
*German: (1): [[Vergangenheit]] ''f''
*Italian: (1, 2): [[passato]] ''m''

===Adjective===
'''past'''

#Having already happened; in the past; finished.
#:''past glories''
#Relating to the past.
#:''past tense''
#(of a period of time) the one before this one
#:''during the past year''

====Translations====
*French: (1, 2): [[passé#French|passé]]
*German: (1): [[vergangen]]
*Italian: (1, 2): [[passato]]

===Adverb===
#in a direction that passes
#:''I watched him walk past''

===Preposition===
#[[beyond]] in place, quantity or time
#:''the room past mine''
#:''count past twenty''
#:''past Midnight''


